# isync / mbsync — Gmail IMAP <-> local Maildir, authenticating with OAuth2.
# Tokens are managed by oama (https://github.com/pdobsan/oama): `oama access`
# prints a fresh access token and refreshes in the background. Requires the
# cyrus-sasl-xoauth2 plugin so isync can speak the XOAUTH2 SASL mechanism.
#
# Per-machine one-time setup (see install-aerc-mail.sh header):
#   1. Create a Google Cloud OAuth client (Desktop app), enable Gmail API
#   2. oama config.yaml: GPG encryption + client_id/client_secret
#   3. oama authorize google <address>     # browser consent, once per account
# Then:  mbsync -a

# ───────────────────────────── av@lab828.com ─────────────────────────────
IMAPAccount av@lab828.com
Host imap.gmail.com
Port 993
User av@lab828.com
PassCmd "oama access av@lab828.com"
TLSType IMAPS
AuthMechs XOAUTH2

IMAPStore av@lab828.com-remote
Account av@lab828.com

MaildirStore av@lab828.com-local
Subfolders Verbatim
Path ~/.local/share/mail/av@lab828.com/
Inbox ~/.local/share/mail/av@lab828.com/INBOX

Channel av@lab828.com
Far :av@lab828.com-remote:
Near :av@lab828.com-local:
Patterns "INBOX" "[Gmail]/Sent Mail" "[Gmail]/Drafts" "[Gmail]/Trash"
Create Both
Expunge Both
SyncState *

